Check for rollout history:
kubectl rollout history deployment nginx-deploy

Create a user, grant him access with private key and csr:
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tls/managing-tls-in-a-cluster/#create-a-certificate-signing-request
Check certificate api version: kubectl api-versions | grep certif
create yaml file for cert: vi john.yaml
copy csr without the master node name and put it under request from john.yaml: (cat john.csr | base64 | tr -d "\n")
create csr cert: kubectl create -f john.yaml
Verify csr cert: kubectl get csr
Approve it: kubectl certificate approve john-developer
Create role: kubectl create role developer --resource=pods --verb=create,list,get --namespace=development
Create rolebinding: kubectl create rolebinding developer-role-binding --role=developer --user=john --namespace=development
Verify access: kubectl auth can-i update pods --namespace=development --as=john

Create a pod, service, test for dns lookup the services and pods:
Create pod: Command at the top
Expose pod (nginx always on port 80): kubectl expose pod nginx --port=80 --target-port=80 --type=ClusterIP --name nginx-service
Test dnslookup for service: kubectl run --generator=run-pod/v1 test-nslookup --image=busybox:1.28 --rm -it -- nslookup nginx-resolver-service > /root/nginx.svc
Test dnslookup for pod (ip of pod hyphen separated): kubectl run --generator=run-pod/v1 test-nslookup --image=busybox:1.28 --rm -it -- nslookup 10-12-13-23.default.pod > /root/nginx.pod

Create a static pod on node01:
Ssh into node01: ssh node01
  Check kubelet status: service kubelet status | systemctl status kubelet
  Enter config file: vi /var/lib/kubelet/config.yaml
  Check for staticPodPath or add it
Ssh into master: 
  create nginx-critical and copy content: kubectl run --generator=run-pod/v1 nginx-critical --image=nginx --dry-run -o yaml > nginx-critical.yaml
SSh into node01:
  Go to staticPodPath and paste the content of yaml file. It will automatically create the pod
  
  
